ğŸ§  Whatâ€™s This About?

This challenge teaches you how to use Netcat (nc) â€” often called the "Swiss Army knife of networking." It's used to send or receive raw data over TCP or UDP connections.

In CTFs and cybersecurity, nc is commonly used to:

    Connect to remote services (like this one!)

    Set up reverse shells

    Create simple servers or listeners

ğŸ› ï¸ Tools Needed:

    Terminal with nc installed
